Another challenge

a bag to fill with sand, a scale and a pulley system.

"Balance of Power"

Each tribe has a giant hanging scale with two platforms.

Each scals is: There is a pulley with two sides: and empty bag and a counterweight. They fill the sandbag to balance the weight, they go to a sand pile to get more sand. There is an extra obstacle on the way to the sand pit (going over a wobbly bridge, balance beam).

Players carry the sand back to the bag with their hands, the sand is hard to carry, falling out of their hands. They put it into the open bags. Twist: If they overfill, they have to dump sand out and try again, wasting time.

Goal: Fill the bag with the exact amount of sand needed to balance the scale perfectly.
Once it balances, a latch releases and drops a key; this is used to unlock a crate to see their reward for the challenge.
